      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(synology-chat,twitch,zalouser): clear timeout timers in Promise.race patterns",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nSeveral extensions use `Promise.race` with `setTimeout`-based timeouts but never clear the timer when the main promise wins the race. When the winning promise resolves/rejects first, the losing `setTimeout` fires later — either rejecting an unlistened promise (causing `unhandledRejection`) or keeping a timer handle alive unnecessarily.\n\n**Affected extensions:**\n- **synology-chat** `webhook-handler.ts`: 120s agent response timeout rejects after nobody is listening\n- **twitch** `probe.ts`: connection timeout rejects after successful connect\n- **zalouser** `probe.ts`: timeout timer keeps running after user info resolves\n\nThis is the same class of bug fixed in the Nostr extension (#39742) — systematic audit found these additional instances.\n\n## Changes\n\nStore timer handles and clear them in `finally` blocks so timers are always cleaned up regardless of which side wins the race.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `npx vitest run extensions/synology-chat/` — all tests pass\n- [x] `npx vitest run extensions/twitch/` — all tests pass\n- [x] `npx vitest run extensions/zalouser/` — all tests pass\n- [x] 309 total tests, 0 failures\n- [x] No functional behavior change — only timer cleanup added",
